00:25:28.810 --> 00:25:31.090 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: HAARP
is intermittent.

00:25:31.090 --> 00:25:32.590 align:middle line:84%
Many people are
under the impression

00:25:32.590 --> 00:25:33.465 align:middle line:90%
it runs all the time.

00:25:33.465 --> 00:25:34.250 align:middle line:90%
It does not.

00:25:34.250 --> 00:25:36.480 align:middle line:84%
They use it for
specific campaigns.

00:25:36.480 --> 00:25:39.576 align:middle line:84%
It's open to academics in
various branches of research

00:25:39.576 --> 00:25:40.950 align:middle line:84%
from around the
world, because it

00:25:40.950 --> 00:25:43.000 align:middle line:90%
is a developmental prototype.

00:25:43.000 --> 00:25:45.340 align:middle line:90%
So it was the first one of many.

00:25:45.340 --> 00:25:47.672 align:middle line:84%
They have now several of
these around the world.

00:25:47.672 --> 00:25:49.130 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: And more
advanced, I bet.

00:25:49.130 --> 00:25:50.588 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: Very
much more advanced.

00:25:50.588 --> 00:25:52.650 align:middle line:84%
In fact, just since
HAARP was developed,

00:25:52.650 --> 00:25:55.540 align:middle line:84%
the size of the arrays
originally anticipated

00:25:55.540 --> 00:25:59.950 align:middle line:84%
have shrunk by kilometers
to be just as effective

00:25:59.950 --> 00:26:02.350 align:middle line:84%
at the smaller level as
they were anticipated

00:26:02.350 --> 00:26:03.815 align:middle line:90%
on a much larger scale.

00:26:03.815 --> 00:26:05.250 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: It's dramatic.

00:26:05.250 --> 00:26:07.970 align:middle line:84%
It's dramatic what they do
and what they have out there.

00:26:07.970 --> 00:26:10.239 align:middle line:84%
Do we know when
HAARP is turned on?

00:26:10.239 --> 00:26:12.530 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: Well, if the people
were monitoring the high

00:26:12.530 --> 00:26:15.730 align:middle line:84%
frequency signal and the broad
range of signals that are

00:26:15.730 --> 00:26:17.830 align:middle line:84%
generated-- is it
primary or secondary?--

00:26:17.830 --> 00:26:21.405 align:middle line:84%
it covers 16 decades, which
is from ultra low frequency

00:26:21.405 --> 00:26:22.260 align:middle line:90%
to visible light.

00:26:22.260 --> 00:26:23.920 align:middle line:84%
This is all the
things that we're

00:26:23.920 --> 00:26:27.700 align:middle line:84%
familiar from radio, TV,
everything in between.

00:26:27.700 --> 00:26:31.270 align:middle line:84%
To monitor that would take a
pretty sophisticated setup.

00:26:31.270 --> 00:26:34.320 align:middle line:84%
And to my knowledge, to
monitor that whole system,

00:26:34.320 --> 00:26:35.790 align:middle line:84%
no one's really
doing that, maybe

00:26:35.790 --> 00:26:38.040 align:middle line:84%
our adversaries, but certainly
not anybody independent

00:26:38.040 --> 00:26:38.890 align:middle line:90%
that I'm aware of.

00:26:38.890 --> 00:26:41.010 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: What about
weather manipulation, Nick?

00:26:41.010 --> 00:26:42.610 align:middle line:84%
Does it have anything
to do with that?

00:26:42.610 --> 00:26:43.276 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Yeah.

00:26:43.276 --> 00:26:44.710 align:middle line:90%
This is an issue that comes up.

00:26:44.710 --> 00:26:46.626 align:middle line:84%
It's one of the other
things that Ben Eastlund

00:26:46.626 --> 00:26:48.510 align:middle line:84%
in his patents
originally talked about.

00:26:48.510 --> 00:26:50.880 align:middle line:84%
They thought it would
take a much larger array.

00:26:50.880 --> 00:26:54.530 align:middle line:84%
Prior do his death in
2005, he did a paper

00:26:54.530 --> 00:26:58.710 align:middle line:84%
for University of Pennsylvania
on weather modification,

00:26:58.710 --> 00:27:01.910 align:middle line:84%
utilizing systems like HAARP
and HAARP specifically.

00:27:01.910 --> 00:27:08.171 align:middle line:84%
And what he said is it needs
1,600 times less energy--

00:27:08.171 --> 00:27:09.670 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: To
manipulate the weather.

00:27:09.670 --> 00:27:11.830 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: --than he originally
anticipated when he first

00:27:11.830 --> 00:27:12.360 align:middle line:90%
designed it.

00:27:12.360 --> 00:27:16.890 align:middle line:84%
So the technology had advanced
between the '80s and 2005

00:27:16.890 --> 00:27:20.960 align:middle line:84%
to the point where 1,600
times less energy to affect

00:27:20.960 --> 00:27:23.885 align:middle line:84%
gravitational waves that then
would drive weather systems

00:27:23.885 --> 00:27:24.910 align:middle line:90%
and weather patterns.

00:27:24.910 --> 00:27:25.890 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely yes.

00:27:25.890 --> 00:27:28.480 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Some people believe
that HAARP is used to create

00:27:28.480 --> 00:27:30.520 align:middle line:90%
earthquakes in other countries.

00:27:30.520 --> 00:27:31.029 align:middle line:90%
Possible?

00:27:31.029 --> 00:27:32.070 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: It's possible.

00:27:32.070 --> 00:27:35.250 align:middle line:84%
This comes, again, from
some of the research.

00:27:35.250 --> 00:27:37.890 align:middle line:84%
Actually, when Secretary
of Defense William Cohen

00:27:37.890 --> 00:27:43.220 align:middle line:84%
was in office, April 27, 1997
he did a DOD news briefing right

00:27:43.220 --> 00:27:45.160 align:middle line:84%
after a lecture on
international terrorism

00:27:45.160 --> 00:27:47.980 align:middle line:84%
and weapons of mass destruction
at the University of Georgia

00:27:47.980 --> 00:27:50.310 align:middle line:84%
where he said that even
terrorist states were

00:27:50.310 --> 00:27:52.650 align:middle line:84%
developing technologies
where they could trigger

00:27:52.650 --> 00:27:56.680 align:middle line:84%
volcanic eruptions, earthquakes,
or weather modification

00:27:56.680 --> 00:27:58.610 align:middle line:90%
utilizing electromagnetic waves.

00:27:58.610 --> 00:27:59.940 align:middle line:90%
And this is the stuff of HAARP.

00:27:59.940 --> 00:28:04.820 align:middle line:84%
We used actually that
material in the course

00:28:04.820 --> 00:28:07.320 align:middle line:84%
of raising this issue
throughout Europe,

00:28:07.320 --> 00:28:09.830 align:middle line:84%
and of course, we had some
success in Europe on this.

00:28:09.830 --> 00:28:13.220 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: What's amazing,
so many people probably

00:28:13.220 --> 00:28:15.150 align:middle line:90%
aren't even aware of HAARP.

00:28:15.150 --> 00:28:17.000 align:middle line:84%
I know people who
watch this show, people

00:28:17.000 --> 00:28:19.052 align:middle line:84%
who listen to Coast to
Coast, they're in on it.

00:28:19.052 --> 00:28:19.760 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Right.

00:28:19.760 --> 00:28:20.940 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: They know
what's going on.

00:28:20.940 --> 00:28:21.648 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Right.

00:28:21.648 --> 00:28:25.050 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: But I would say that
most Americans, most Canadians,

00:28:25.050 --> 00:28:29.131 align:middle line:84%
most people on this planet
would have no idea what's going

00:28:29.131 --> 00:28:29.630 align:middle line:90%
on here.

00:28:29.630 --> 00:28:30.170 align:middle line:90%
Would you agree?

00:28:30.170 --> 00:28:31.420 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: I absolutely agree.

00:28:31.420 --> 00:28:35.380 align:middle line:84%
And we've been at this a
long time on these issues,

00:28:35.380 --> 00:28:40.490 align:middle line:84%
now 17 years, and I've done
3,000 radio broadcasts,

00:28:40.490 --> 00:28:42.360 align:middle line:84%
80 of them with
you guys at Coast,

00:28:42.360 --> 00:28:46.310 align:middle line:84%
and lots of television, lots
of things, and lots of print,

00:28:46.310 --> 00:28:49.900 align:middle line:84%
but these kinds of issues just
escape most people's attention.

00:28:49.900 --> 00:28:50.750 align:middle line:90%
It's technical.

00:28:50.750 --> 00:28:52.400 align:middle line:90%
People kind of ignore it.

00:28:52.400 --> 00:28:54.710 align:middle line:84%
But in our societies
and our cultures today,

00:28:54.710 --> 00:28:56.330 align:middle line:84%
having a base
knowledge of science

00:28:56.330 --> 00:28:57.520 align:middle line:90%
is incredibly important.

00:28:57.520 --> 00:29:00.300 align:middle line:84%
What makes governments
powerful in the 21st century

00:29:00.300 --> 00:29:02.490 align:middle line:84%
is command and control
of high technology.

00:29:02.490 --> 00:29:04.520 align:middle line:84%
When you think of the Congress,
when you think of the Senate,

00:29:04.520 --> 00:29:06.910 align:middle line:84%
how many scientists do we have
there making the decisions

00:29:06.910 --> 00:29:08.065 align:middle line:90%
for us?

00:29:08.065 --> 00:29:08.940 align:middle line:90%
None, virtually none.

00:29:08.940 --> 00:29:09.770 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Right.

00:29:09.770 --> 00:29:12.650 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: This is a problem
in a technological world where

00:29:12.650 --> 00:29:14.402 align:middle line:90%
so much is driven by technology.

00:29:14.402 --> 00:29:16.860 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: You know how sometimes
in the morning you wake up

00:29:16.860 --> 00:29:18.250 align:middle line:90%
and you just feel great, right?

00:29:18.250 --> 00:29:18.970 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Right.

00:29:18.970 --> 00:29:22.370 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: And then other days
you feel a little sluggish.

00:29:22.370 --> 00:29:25.650 align:middle line:84%
You just feel like you're
off kilter a little bit.

00:29:25.650 --> 00:29:30.930 align:middle line:84%
Could it be because technology
like HAARP is turned on

00:29:30.930 --> 00:29:32.274 align:middle line:90%
and it's affecting us somehow?

00:29:32.274 --> 00:29:33.190 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Absolutely.

00:29:33.190 --> 00:29:37.015 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the idea that this
is being tested generally,

00:29:37.015 --> 00:29:38.890 align:middle line:84%
it's being tested by
not just our government.

00:29:38.890 --> 00:29:41.115 align:middle line:84%
The Chinese government
has advanced technologies

00:29:41.115 --> 00:29:41.900 align:middle line:90%
in this area.

00:29:41.900 --> 00:29:45.790 align:middle line:84%
The CIA released some documents
from their military journals

00:29:45.790 --> 00:29:46.990 align:middle line:90%
that were pretty revealing.

00:29:46.990 --> 00:29:48.780 align:middle line:90%
They parallel us exactly.

00:29:48.780 --> 00:29:50.750 align:middle line:84%
The Russians
actually pre-date us

00:29:50.750 --> 00:29:53.050 align:middle line:84%
on a lot of this technology
because of the method

00:29:53.050 --> 00:29:55.320 align:middle line:84%
in which they integrated
their science.

00:29:55.320 --> 00:29:58.280 align:middle line:84%
But they're the leaders in
this type of technology.

00:29:58.280 --> 00:30:00.451 align:middle line:84%
And when you think about
it, people sort of downplay

00:30:00.451 --> 00:30:01.825 align:middle line:84%
these countries
and say, oh, they

00:30:01.825 --> 00:30:03.658 align:middle line:84%
don't have that much
money in their budgets.

00:30:03.658 --> 00:30:04.640 align:middle line:90%
It's not a big deal.

00:30:04.640 --> 00:30:09.310 align:middle line:84%
But look at what you buy in
China for the same dollar.

00:30:09.310 --> 00:30:12.000 align:middle line:84%
You get a technician over
there for $1,000 a month,

00:30:12.000 --> 00:30:15.530 align:middle line:84%
maybe if they're lucky, that
you might pay $10,000 a month

00:30:15.530 --> 00:30:17.010 align:middle line:90%
for same skill set in the US.

00:30:17.010 --> 00:30:19.030 align:middle line:84%
So you get a lot more
bang for your buck.

00:30:19.030 --> 00:30:20.530 align:middle line:84%
You've got a
centralized government.

00:30:20.530 --> 00:30:22.620 align:middle line:84%
You've got centralized
intelligence, really,

00:30:22.620 --> 00:30:24.470 align:middle line:84%
because the brightest
minds end up

00:30:24.470 --> 00:30:28.170 align:middle line:84%
in these kinds of fields working
for military applications.

00:30:28.170 --> 00:30:30.410 align:middle line:84%
In the US, our
government does not

00:30:30.410 --> 00:30:33.590 align:middle line:84%
engage in fundamental
research by military budgets

00:30:33.590 --> 00:30:36.100 align:middle line:84%
for anything but
military applications,

00:30:36.100 --> 00:30:37.230 align:middle line:90%
not for basic science.

00:30:37.230 --> 00:30:41.250 align:middle line:84%
And this is where this issue
has become increasingly more

00:30:41.250 --> 00:30:44.670 align:middle line:84%
important for the general public
because the science is being

00:30:44.670 --> 00:30:48.450 align:middle line:84%
advanced also by private parties
and non-governmental entities.

00:30:48.450 --> 00:30:51.960 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Is there something
that could go wrong with HAARP

00:30:51.960 --> 00:30:56.010 align:middle line:84%
or mind control technology
with the dark side of some kind

00:30:56.010 --> 00:30:58.339 align:middle line:90%
of horrible mistake?

00:30:58.339 --> 00:31:00.130 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: There's
always that possibility.

00:31:00.130 --> 00:31:03.790 align:middle line:84%
The idea that operators
are experimenting

00:31:03.790 --> 00:31:06.440 align:middle line:84%
without constraint, the
fact that it happens.

00:31:06.440 --> 00:31:09.910 align:middle line:84%
Secretary of Energy O'Leary said
over half a million US victims

00:31:09.910 --> 00:31:12.920 align:middle line:84%
of human experimentation
in the United States

00:31:12.920 --> 00:31:16.010 align:middle line:84%
never notified, never talked
to, never consented to.

00:31:16.010 --> 00:31:20.380 align:middle line:84%
The fact that they would
experiment on mass populations,

00:31:20.380 --> 00:31:21.300 align:middle line:90%
this is the case.

00:31:21.300 --> 00:31:24.670 align:middle line:84%
And the rationale is, oh, but
the aftereffect is harmless.

00:31:24.670 --> 00:31:26.850 align:middle line:84%
The triggering
effect, suppose you

00:31:26.850 --> 00:31:29.240 align:middle line:84%
create a general
sense of anxiety

00:31:29.240 --> 00:31:31.490 align:middle line:84%
when there's other
events going on,

00:31:31.490 --> 00:31:34.550 align:middle line:84%
and then you trigger
perhaps a riot,

00:31:34.550 --> 00:31:36.540 align:middle line:84%
just because the tension's
already building,

00:31:36.540 --> 00:31:39.840 align:middle line:84%
and then you add that extra
straw on the camel's back.

00:31:39.840 --> 00:31:41.490 align:middle line:84%
Those are the kinds
of things that

00:31:41.490 --> 00:31:43.950 align:middle line:84%
would be highly
disconcerting to all of us.

00:31:43.950 --> 00:31:47.490 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: We used to laugh when
people would say I hear voices.

00:31:47.490 --> 00:31:48.579 align:middle line:90%
I hear voices.

00:31:48.579 --> 00:31:49.620 align:middle line:90%
People are talking to me.

00:31:49.620 --> 00:31:51.431 align:middle line:90%
You thought they were nuts.

00:31:51.431 --> 00:31:52.680 align:middle line:90%
I don't laugh at that anymore.

00:31:52.680 --> 00:31:53.263 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: No.

00:31:53.263 --> 00:31:55.040 align:middle line:84%
In fact, there's
some good technology,

00:31:55.040 --> 00:31:56.540 align:middle line:84%
and later in the
program we're going

00:31:56.540 --> 00:31:59.110 align:middle line:84%
to demonstrate some
that's hardwired.

00:31:59.110 --> 00:32:04.680 align:middle line:84%
But Woody Norris was a scientist
that won the MIT-Lemelson Award

00:32:04.680 --> 00:32:07.280 align:middle line:84%
in 2005, I believe
it was, and it

00:32:07.280 --> 00:32:10.106 align:middle line:90%
was for acoustic heterodyning.

00:32:10.106 --> 00:32:11.730 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Did he
invent the flying car?

00:32:11.730 --> 00:32:12.640 align:middle line:90%
Was that the same guy?

00:32:12.640 --> 00:32:13.460 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: I don't know
if it's the same guy.

00:32:13.460 --> 00:32:14.720 align:middle line:90%
He's pretty prolific inventor.

00:32:14.720 --> 00:32:15.803 align:middle line:90%
He's done a lot of things.

00:32:15.803 --> 00:32:19.374 align:middle line:84%
But in this technology, he could
send a signal across a room,

00:32:19.374 --> 00:32:21.290 align:middle line:84%
hitting a particular
person in your audience--

00:32:21.290 --> 00:32:22.160 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Aim right at them.

00:32:22.160 --> 00:32:24.410 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: --aim right at them,
and they would hear a voice

00:32:24.410 --> 00:32:24.993 align:middle line:90%
in their head.

00:32:24.993 --> 00:32:27.660 align:middle line:84%
And they sold that
technology or licensed it

00:32:27.660 --> 00:32:30.632 align:middle line:84%
to the military
for security fences

00:32:30.632 --> 00:32:32.340 align:middle line:84%
so that when you got
into a certain range

00:32:32.340 --> 00:32:35.494 align:middle line:84%
you'd hear this voice from
nowhere telling you what to do.

00:32:35.494 --> 00:32:37.410 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: You would think
it was godly, right?

00:32:37.410 --> 00:32:38.394 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Absolutely.

00:32:38.394 --> 00:32:38.935 align:middle line:90%
And internal.

00:32:38.935 --> 00:32:41.980 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't originate
here with the ears,

00:32:41.980 --> 00:32:43.850 align:middle line:90%
so it's like it's in your head.

00:32:43.850 --> 00:32:46.160 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Well, when we
think as human beings,

00:32:46.160 --> 00:32:48.300 align:middle line:84%
whether you're driving
a car or whatever,

00:32:48.300 --> 00:32:53.060 align:middle line:84%
that person who is you, you can
hear that voice talking to you,

00:32:53.060 --> 00:32:53.560 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:32:53.560 --> 00:32:57.470 align:middle line:84%
When you make a right-hand
turn and you do it naturally,

00:32:57.470 --> 00:33:00.550 align:middle line:84%
but you can sometimes hear
your voice of yourself just

00:33:00.550 --> 00:33:03.310 align:middle line:90%
saying turn or do this, do that.

00:33:03.310 --> 00:33:05.232 align:middle line:90%
Is it that kind of thing?

00:33:05.232 --> 00:33:06.940 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: It could
be as subtle as that.

00:33:06.940 --> 00:33:10.870 align:middle line:84%
It could even be below the
level of conscious awareness

00:33:10.870 --> 00:33:12.280 align:middle line:84%
and still have a
profound effect.

00:33:12.280 --> 00:33:14.915 align:middle line:84%
In fact, there was a technology
used to dissuade shoplifters.

00:33:14.915 --> 00:33:16.280 align:middle line:90%
It was used in Japan.

00:33:16.280 --> 00:33:19.525 align:middle line:84%
And in seven languages
they had these messages.

00:33:19.525 --> 00:33:20.150 align:middle line:90%
And they were--

00:33:20.150 --> 00:33:20.750 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Bombarding them.

00:33:20.750 --> 00:33:22.416 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: --below
the level of hearing,

00:33:22.416 --> 00:33:23.900 align:middle line:84%
so you didn't really
perceive them.

00:33:23.900 --> 00:33:26.320 align:middle line:84%
But they had a 40%
reduction in theft.

00:33:26.320 --> 00:33:27.130 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Amazing.

00:33:27.130 --> 00:33:28.360 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: And so it works.

00:33:28.360 --> 00:33:29.670 align:middle line:90%
Now why only 40%?

00:33:29.670 --> 00:33:33.090 align:middle line:84%
Well, most theft, people
say, in shoplifting

00:33:33.090 --> 00:33:34.795 align:middle line:84%
is professional
gangs who've already

00:33:34.795 --> 00:33:36.170 align:middle line:90%
suspended their consciousness.

00:33:36.170 --> 00:33:37.740 align:middle line:84%
They've already
made the decision.

00:33:37.740 --> 00:33:38.570 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: They're
there to steal.

00:33:38.570 --> 00:33:40.528 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: They don't
care what the message is.

00:33:40.528 --> 00:33:43.520 align:middle line:84%
The other 40% is probably
people, mostly children,

00:33:43.520 --> 00:33:45.960 align:middle line:84%
young people, who are making
bad decisions who still have

00:33:45.960 --> 00:33:48.095 align:middle line:84%
a consciousness that's
working that says,

00:33:48.095 --> 00:33:49.120 align:middle line:90%
oh, I shouldn't do this.

00:33:49.120 --> 00:33:51.110 align:middle line:84%
And then they get the message
in their own language saying

00:33:51.110 --> 00:33:52.276 align:middle line:90%
don't do it, and they don't.

00:33:52.276 --> 00:33:55.060 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Could you bombard
people if you wanted to make

00:33:55.060 --> 00:34:00.790 align:middle line:84%
them go home early, curfews
for example, and just shoot it,

00:34:00.790 --> 00:34:04.140 align:middle line:84%
go home, get off the street
without a big megaphone?

00:34:04.140 --> 00:34:05.999 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: You could
do all of that,

00:34:05.999 --> 00:34:07.540 align:middle line:84%
and you would have
a profound effect.

00:34:07.540 --> 00:34:09.998 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure it would parallel
the same kind of effect they

00:34:09.998 --> 00:34:11.299 align:middle line:90%
had.

00:34:11.299 --> 00:34:12.340 align:middle line:90%
Some people aren't going.

00:34:12.340 --> 00:34:14.260 align:middle line:90%
They're not going to cooperate.

00:34:14.260 --> 00:34:16.230 align:middle line:84%
But I think that is
exactly the case.

00:34:16.230 --> 00:34:17.954 align:middle line:84%
And when you look at
it on a mass scale,

00:34:17.954 --> 00:34:20.120 align:middle line:84%
again when you think about
it from advertising, when

00:34:20.120 --> 00:34:22.690 align:middle line:84%
you think about it from--
for political purposes,

00:34:22.690 --> 00:34:26.290 align:middle line:84%
or, say, in a situation
where general unrest,

00:34:26.290 --> 00:34:28.610 align:middle line:84%
would our government use
that to calm a population?

00:34:28.610 --> 00:34:30.230 align:middle line:90%
I think absolutely yes.

00:34:30.230 --> 00:34:31.639 align:middle line:90%
There's no doubt in my mind.

00:34:31.639 --> 00:34:36.090 align:middle line:84%
Coming out of government, two
generations of government,

00:34:36.090 --> 00:34:37.350 align:middle line:90%
they would indeed.

00:34:37.350 --> 00:34:41.520 align:middle line:84%
Because it's considered less
intrusive than tear gas,

00:34:41.520 --> 00:34:43.929 align:middle line:84%
where people do die from
that, have lung disorders--

00:34:43.929 --> 00:34:44.090 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Exactly.

00:34:44.090 --> 00:34:44.400 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: --and so on.

00:34:44.400 --> 00:34:46.110 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Does not
knock down buildings.

00:34:46.110 --> 00:34:46.912 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Right.

00:34:46.912 --> 00:34:48.370 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
rebuild anything.

00:34:48.370 --> 00:34:49.650 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Exactly.

00:34:49.650 --> 00:34:51.280 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: From a
lot of perspectives,

00:34:51.280 --> 00:34:52.929 align:middle line:90%
this is the idealized weapon.

00:34:52.929 --> 00:34:56.640 align:middle line:84%
Even during the first Gulf
War, and if you remember in

00:34:56.640 --> 00:34:58.890 align:middle line:84%
that there was, I think it
was the fourth largest army

00:34:58.890 --> 00:35:01.505 align:middle line:84%
in the world at the time, and
they were giving up en masse.

00:35:01.505 --> 00:35:02.750 align:middle line:90%
No one could figure it out.

00:35:02.750 --> 00:35:04.570 align:middle line:84%
And it was Scottish
media that reported

00:35:04.570 --> 00:35:07.380 align:middle line:84%
that we used a signal
that we embedded

00:35:07.380 --> 00:35:09.897 align:middle line:84%
on the broadcast bringing
the Muslim music and prayers

00:35:09.897 --> 00:35:11.730 align:middle line:84%
that they were all
listening to that created

00:35:11.730 --> 00:35:14.610 align:middle line:84%
a general sense of anxiety
and fear to the point

00:35:14.610 --> 00:35:17.934 align:middle line:84%
where people were surrendering
en masse to two or three--

00:35:17.934 --> 00:35:19.100 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Just giving it up.

00:35:19.100 --> 00:35:19.630 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Just giving it up.

00:35:19.630 --> 00:35:20.690 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: That was
amazing technology.

00:35:20.690 --> 00:35:22.190 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: And that
is a technology.

00:35:22.190 --> 00:35:24.330 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Have we gotten
too far technologically?

00:35:24.330 --> 00:35:25.810 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: I think we have.

00:35:25.810 --> 00:35:27.910 align:middle line:84%
I think the domain of
interfering with human brain

00:35:27.910 --> 00:35:30.830 align:middle line:84%
performance, it's a
violation of free will.

00:35:30.830 --> 00:35:34.260 align:middle line:84%
Most religious traditions say
that God won't even do that,

00:35:34.260 --> 00:35:37.580 align:middle line:84%
and yet here's man playing
with the consciousness

00:35:37.580 --> 00:35:39.420 align:middle line:84%
of other individuals
without their consent.

00:35:39.420 --> 00:35:43.990 align:middle line:84%
I think it's the greatest
threat to freedom, to liberty,

00:35:43.990 --> 00:35:48.840 align:middle line:84%
to the things that we hold
sacred in this country,

00:35:48.840 --> 00:35:51.680 align:middle line:84%
and I think it's the wrong
direction for government to go.

00:35:51.680 --> 00:35:54.080 align:middle line:84%
And it also, because
it's classified

00:35:54.080 --> 00:35:58.120 align:middle line:84%
it denies other researchers
in the health sciences

00:35:58.120 --> 00:35:59.670 align:middle line:84%
opportunities to
access information

00:35:59.670 --> 00:36:02.790 align:middle line:84%
that might help address brain
disorders, other things.

00:36:02.790 --> 00:36:05.290 align:middle line:84%
Because we're learning a lot,
and then we're classifying it.

00:36:05.290 --> 00:36:07.120 align:middle line:90%
That's a big loss.

00:36:07.120 --> 00:36:09.570 align:middle line:84%
And then we're not having
the public debate about where

00:36:09.570 --> 00:36:12.390 align:middle line:84%
this technology really fits
in, like we are about privacy

00:36:12.390 --> 00:36:14.850 align:middle line:84%
issues today and beginning
that more lively debate.

00:36:14.850 --> 00:36:17.410 align:middle line:84%
These are fundamental
privacy issues.

00:36:17.410 --> 00:36:20.390 align:middle line:84%
This is the root of all
privacy, is the human mind.

00:36:20.390 --> 00:36:24.390 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: The president wants
to spend $100 million on brain

00:36:24.390 --> 00:36:25.070 align:middle line:90%
research.

00:36:25.070 --> 00:36:26.240 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Right.

00:36:26.240 --> 00:36:28.820 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: One would
say, hey, this is great.

00:36:28.820 --> 00:36:31.632 align:middle line:84%
Another thought would
be, what's going on here?

00:36:31.632 --> 00:36:32.340 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Right.

00:36:32.340 --> 00:36:35.590 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: I suspect everything
we've talked about right now is

00:36:35.590 --> 00:36:38.040 align:middle line:90%
primarily black ops budgets?

00:36:38.040 --> 00:36:39.230 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Yeah, it is.

00:36:39.230 --> 00:36:42.240 align:middle line:84%
In fact, back in the '90s
up to 40% of the equipment

00:36:42.240 --> 00:36:44.280 align:middle line:84%
budget for the Air
Force was black,

00:36:44.280 --> 00:36:46.779 align:middle line:84%
where even the Congress didn't
know what they were funding.

00:36:46.779 --> 00:36:48.820 align:middle line:84%
And here's the thing about
when the Congress goes

00:36:48.820 --> 00:36:52.300 align:middle line:84%
into these closed hearings
that are classified hearings,

00:36:52.300 --> 00:36:53.710 align:middle line:90%
they can't bring their staff.

00:36:53.710 --> 00:36:55.180 align:middle line:90%
They can't take notes.

00:36:55.180 --> 00:36:57.906 align:middle line:84%
They can't talk about
this to anyone else.

00:36:57.906 --> 00:36:59.364 align:middle line:84%
So here we have a
bunch of people--

00:36:59.364 --> 00:37:00.860 align:middle line:84%
it would be the equivalent
of putting a five-year-old

00:37:00.860 --> 00:37:02.670 align:middle line:84%
in the room, because they don't
have the technical knowledge

00:37:02.670 --> 00:37:05.140 align:middle line:84%
even to challenge what
they're being presented

00:37:05.140 --> 00:37:07.410 align:middle line:84%
and ask the kind of
questions that we

00:37:07.410 --> 00:37:09.230 align:middle line:84%
expect our
representatives to ask.

00:37:09.230 --> 00:37:10.730 align:middle line:90%
This is where the hole is.

00:37:10.730 --> 00:37:13.330 align:middle line:84%
The secrecy syndrome
has driven us completely

00:37:13.330 --> 00:37:16.490 align:middle line:84%
in the wrong direction without
the experts in the right place

00:37:16.490 --> 00:37:18.870 align:middle line:84%
with the right power
to make the judgments.

00:37:18.870 --> 00:37:20.510 align:middle line:84%
And so it's left
to bureaucracies

00:37:20.510 --> 00:37:21.890 align:middle line:90%
to make those judgments.

00:37:21.890 --> 00:37:23.990 align:middle line:84%
And their mission,
the military's mission

00:37:23.990 --> 00:37:25.394 align:middle line:90%
is a paranoid mission.

00:37:25.394 --> 00:37:27.060 align:middle line:84%
People who would deal
with these issues,

00:37:27.060 --> 00:37:28.184 align:middle line:90%
we're always accusing them.

00:37:28.184 --> 00:37:29.250 align:middle line:90%
You're paranoid.

00:37:29.250 --> 00:37:32.110 align:middle line:84%
The military's job is to look
at every possibility that

00:37:32.110 --> 00:37:35.400 align:middle line:84%
can come against the country
and devise a plan against it.

00:37:35.400 --> 00:37:36.870 align:middle line:90%
That's paranoid thinking.

00:37:36.870 --> 00:37:39.380 align:middle line:84%
That's why we keep the
military in the closet

00:37:39.380 --> 00:37:42.480 align:middle line:84%
and the civilian sector in
this country makes decisions.

00:37:42.480 --> 00:37:44.170 align:middle line:84%
But how can you make
decisions and how

00:37:44.170 --> 00:37:46.207 align:middle line:84%
can you hold them accountable
when you can't ask

00:37:46.207 --> 00:37:47.040 align:middle line:90%
the right questions?

00:37:47.040 --> 00:37:48.700 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Or you even
know what's going on.

00:37:48.700 --> 00:37:49.320 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Right.

00:37:49.320 --> 00:37:50.260 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: How about the senator?

00:37:50.260 --> 00:37:51.190 align:middle line:90%
How does he react?

00:37:51.190 --> 00:37:54.670 align:middle line:84%
Knowing you, you're his
brother and all this knowledge

00:37:54.670 --> 00:37:57.341 align:middle line:84%
that you possess,
what does he do?

00:37:57.341 --> 00:37:58.340 align:middle line:90%
How does he handle that?

00:37:58.340 --> 00:38:00.360 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: Well,
Mark is a freshman.

00:38:00.360 --> 00:38:01.950 align:middle line:84%
He's up for
re-election next year.

00:38:01.950 --> 00:38:04.040 align:middle line:84%
I think with his
re-election he's

00:38:04.040 --> 00:38:05.920 align:middle line:90%
established his credibility.

00:38:05.920 --> 00:38:08.230 align:middle line:84%
What we've talked
about a lot is the idea

00:38:08.230 --> 00:38:10.290 align:middle line:90%
of bringing forward the science.

00:38:10.290 --> 00:38:12.930 align:middle line:84%
And some of his colleagues
have asked for our information.

00:38:12.930 --> 00:38:14.300 align:middle line:90%
We've passed it on.

00:38:14.300 --> 00:38:16.850 align:middle line:84%
I think that's eventually
going to happen.

00:38:16.850 --> 00:38:18.050 align:middle line:90%
It's a controversial issue.

00:38:18.050 --> 00:38:18.500 align:middle line:90%
It's going to take--

00:38:18.500 --> 00:38:18.710 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: It's huge.

00:38:18.710 --> 00:38:19.150 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: --a lot of work.

00:38:19.150 --> 00:38:20.566 align:middle line:84%
And it is something
that you can't

00:38:20.566 --> 00:38:24.614 align:middle line:84%
do without now
non-governmental organizations.

00:38:24.614 --> 00:38:25.280 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Right.

00:38:25.280 --> 00:38:27.821 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: Because you've got
535 people you got to establish

00:38:27.821 --> 00:38:28.870 align:middle line:90%
communication with.

00:38:28.870 --> 00:38:31.329 align:middle line:84%
That's a big task, between 100
in the Senate and the House.

00:38:31.329 --> 00:38:33.120 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: And some
won't even believe this.

00:38:33.120 --> 00:38:33.950 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Right.

00:38:33.950 --> 00:38:35.410 align:middle line:90%
The science is good.

00:38:35.410 --> 00:38:36.420 align:middle line:90%
We've documented it.

00:38:36.420 --> 00:38:38.327 align:middle line:84%
Anyone who's read our
material recognizes

00:38:38.327 --> 00:38:40.160 align:middle line:84%
that we footnote
everything, and they're not

00:38:40.160 --> 00:38:41.600 align:middle line:90%
conversations in phone booths.

00:38:41.600 --> 00:38:44.320 align:middle line:84%
They're legitimate
academic records.

00:38:44.320 --> 00:38:46.990 align:middle line:84%
There are those that have
started to come forward.

00:38:46.990 --> 00:38:49.060 align:middle line:84%
I think we're going
to see more of that.

00:38:49.060 --> 00:38:51.580 align:middle line:84%
What we really need is
whistleblower mechanisms,

00:38:51.580 --> 00:38:53.330 align:middle line:84%
not just for this area
but for many areas,

00:38:53.330 --> 00:38:55.705 align:middle line:84%
not just for government but
for the private sector, which

00:38:55.705 --> 00:38:57.910 align:middle line:84%
is exempt from the Freedom
of Information Act, where

00:38:57.910 --> 00:38:59.820 align:middle line:90%
a lot of this gets farmed out.

00:38:59.820 --> 00:39:02.994 align:middle line:84%
We need a more open society,
not a more closed one.

00:39:02.994 --> 00:39:05.160 align:middle line:84%
And we are headed absolutely
in the wrong direction,

00:39:05.160 --> 00:39:07.310 align:middle line:84%
the opposite direction
of where we need to go.

00:39:07.310 --> 00:39:09.685 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Let's take some more
questions for Nick Begich.

00:39:09.685 --> 00:39:11.490 align:middle line:90%
Yes, right up here in the front.

00:39:11.490 --> 00:39:13.820 align:middle line:84%
>> AUDIENCE: Having
this level of awareness

00:39:13.820 --> 00:39:17.360 align:middle line:84%
of the manipulations and what
you would might call the dark

00:39:17.360 --> 00:39:21.760 align:middle line:84%
side, what keeps
you going every day?

00:39:21.760 --> 00:39:24.070 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: I get asked
that a lot over the years.

00:39:24.070 --> 00:39:29.620 align:middle line:84%
And I'm a pathological optimist
is the way I've described it.

00:39:29.620 --> 00:39:32.230 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: I knew you were
a pathological something.

00:39:32.230 --> 00:39:36.260 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: And really, I like
the technologies that I study.

00:39:36.260 --> 00:39:38.100 align:middle line:84%
I study a broad range
of technologies,

00:39:38.100 --> 00:39:40.430 align:middle line:84%
and they're exciting to
me at a lot of levels.

00:39:40.430 --> 00:39:44.520 align:middle line:84%
The thing I look at in this
is the potential for enhancing

00:39:44.520 --> 00:39:47.180 align:middle line:84%
our performance
is so phenomenal.

00:39:47.180 --> 00:39:50.170 align:middle line:84%
The next evolution, the next
leap that many are looking at

00:39:50.170 --> 00:39:52.440 align:middle line:84%
is what we used to call
extrasensory perceptions

00:39:52.440 --> 00:39:55.885 align:middle line:84%
or the military now calls
anomalous human capacities

00:39:55.885 --> 00:39:57.540 align:middle line:90%
or capabilities.

00:39:57.540 --> 00:39:58.709 align:middle line:90%
Maybe that is our next leap.

00:39:58.709 --> 00:40:00.875 align:middle line:84%
When you think about making
government accountable--

00:40:00.875 --> 00:40:03.310 align:middle line:84%
and they're experimenting with
electronic telepathy today--

00:40:03.310 --> 00:40:04.185 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Constantly.

00:40:04.185 --> 00:40:07.759 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: --imagine if we
knew what our leaders thought.

00:40:07.759 --> 00:40:09.050 align:middle line:90%
Now that would change the game.

00:40:09.050 --> 00:40:11.174 align:middle line:84%
It would also create an
environment where all of us

00:40:11.174 --> 00:40:13.605 align:middle line:90%
had our judgement day, right?

00:40:13.605 --> 00:40:15.480 align:middle line:84%
Because we have to be
forgiving of ourselves,

00:40:15.480 --> 00:40:16.896 align:middle line:84%
we have to be
forgiving of others,

00:40:16.896 --> 00:40:18.687 align:middle line:84%
high characteristics
for human beings.

00:40:18.687 --> 00:40:20.520 align:middle line:84%
The challenge is to
address our technologies

00:40:20.520 --> 00:40:24.000 align:middle line:84%
to enhance the human
potential, not to restrict it.

00:40:24.000 --> 00:40:27.370 align:middle line:90%
And this is a huge opportunity.

00:40:27.370 --> 00:40:31.760 align:middle line:84%
It is the next wave of challenge
that can change this planet.

00:40:31.760 --> 00:40:33.495 align:middle line:84%
It is what will
change this planet.

00:40:33.495 --> 00:40:34.787 align:middle line:90%
So that's what keeps me going.

00:40:34.787 --> 00:40:35.620 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: All right.

00:40:35.620 --> 00:40:37.810 align:middle line:84%
And Nick, we also use
high technology here

00:40:37.810 --> 00:40:40.970 align:middle line:84%
on "Beyond Belief," so let's
take a question from somewhere

00:40:40.970 --> 00:40:42.974 align:middle line:90%
out there for Nick Begich.

00:40:42.974 --> 00:40:43.890 align:middle line:90%
>> AUDIENCE: Hi, Nick.

00:40:43.890 --> 00:40:46.040 align:middle line:84%
I'm Tricia from Idaho,
and I was wondering

00:40:46.040 --> 00:40:47.890 align:middle line:84%
what the positives
versus the negatives

00:40:47.890 --> 00:40:51.334 align:middle line:84%
are when it comes
to mind control.

00:40:51.334 --> 00:40:52.500 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: A great question.

00:40:52.500 --> 00:40:54.749 align:middle line:84%
And again, getting to the
positive, some of the things

00:40:54.749 --> 00:40:57.780 align:middle line:84%
that you can do
with mind effects.

00:40:57.780 --> 00:41:01.196 align:middle line:84%
The idea of
enhancing learning is

00:41:01.196 --> 00:41:02.570 align:middle line:84%
one of the
fundamentals, the idea

00:41:02.570 --> 00:41:05.710 align:middle line:84%
of being able to put
your brain into a state

00:41:05.710 --> 00:41:08.780 align:middle line:84%
where you can absorb
information more readily.

00:41:08.780 --> 00:41:10.830 align:middle line:90%
You can commit it to memory.

00:41:10.830 --> 00:41:14.725 align:middle line:84%
Children that are
hyperactive or brain activity

00:41:14.725 --> 00:41:17.380 align:middle line:84%
is running slow,
running too slow,

00:41:17.380 --> 00:41:21.410 align:middle line:84%
you can actually train them
through biofeedback techniques

00:41:21.410 --> 00:41:23.982 align:middle line:84%
to hit that ideal
zone of learning.

00:41:23.982 --> 00:41:25.940 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Can you make
smarter people that way?

00:41:25.940 --> 00:41:26.780 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Absolutely.

00:41:26.780 --> 00:41:27.955 align:middle line:84%
And not only can you
make smarter people,

00:41:27.955 --> 00:41:30.460 align:middle line:84%
but you can take children that
are having these difficulties

00:41:30.460 --> 00:41:32.880 align:middle line:84%
that we're now drugging
on a mass scale--

00:41:32.880 --> 00:41:34.770 align:middle line:84%
and the place where
this has been done,

00:41:34.770 --> 00:41:37.300 align:middle line:84%
as many as 80% of the
student population that were

00:41:37.300 --> 00:41:39.984 align:middle line:84%
on psychoactive drugs were
able to get off of them--

00:41:39.984 --> 00:41:40.900 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: That's good.

00:41:40.900 --> 00:41:44.050 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: --and then go right
to that super learning state

00:41:44.050 --> 00:41:46.350 align:middle line:84%
at will with just a
little bit of training.

00:41:46.350 --> 00:41:49.300 align:middle line:84%
That's exciting to
me and for all of us.

00:41:49.300 --> 00:41:51.369 align:middle line:84%
Think about trying
to think clearly

00:41:51.369 --> 00:41:52.410 align:middle line:90%
when you're under stress.

00:41:52.410 --> 00:41:53.390 align:middle line:90%
Most of us are.

00:41:53.390 --> 00:41:56.600 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the thing that inhibits
our reaching our higher states

00:41:56.600 --> 00:42:01.330 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness is stress,
because your brain cannot reach

00:42:01.330 --> 00:42:04.435 align:middle line:84%
the slower rhythmic levels as
long as you're in that state.

00:42:04.435 --> 00:42:06.435 align:middle line:84%
So if you really want to
control the population,

00:42:06.435 --> 00:42:09.880 align:middle line:84%
the most simple way is keep
a sense of general anxiety

00:42:09.880 --> 00:42:10.660 align:middle line:90%
out there.

00:42:10.660 --> 00:42:11.590 align:middle line:90%
That's the enemy.

00:42:11.590 --> 00:42:12.340 align:middle line:90%
Fear is the enemy.

00:42:12.340 --> 00:42:13.214 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Absolutely.

00:42:13.214 --> 00:42:15.374 align:middle line:84%
And they do a good job
at that, don't they?

00:42:15.374 --> 00:42:17.540 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: Whether it's an
advertiser worrying about

00:42:17.540 --> 00:42:20.870 align:middle line:84%
your deodorant or your teeth,
or whether it's a politician,

00:42:20.870 --> 00:42:22.640 align:middle line:84%
or whether it's
the news broadcast,

00:42:22.640 --> 00:42:24.260 align:middle line:90%
that's really the root.

00:42:24.260 --> 00:42:29.730 align:middle line:84%
If we can begin to find ways
to combat, and there are ways,

00:42:29.730 --> 00:42:32.760 align:middle line:84%
that's where, again, we can
reach these higher capacities

00:42:32.760 --> 00:42:35.520 align:middle line:84%
where our brains function
more efficiently, where

00:42:35.520 --> 00:42:37.790 align:middle line:84%
we make better decisions,
where we perhaps

00:42:37.790 --> 00:42:39.940 align:middle line:84%
trigger these anomalous
capabilities as well.

00:42:39.940 --> 00:42:43.060 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: I've wondered, even in
my radio show Coast to Coast AM

00:42:43.060 --> 00:42:47.230 align:middle line:84%
if I went on every night,
every night and went, well,

00:42:47.230 --> 00:42:49.890 align:middle line:84%
everything's going well
today, and it was a nice day,

00:42:49.890 --> 00:42:53.970 align:middle line:84%
dah dah dah dah dah-- you have
to look at all those other

00:42:53.970 --> 00:42:57.490 align:middle line:84%
aspects of darkness
and danger and stuff.

00:42:57.490 --> 00:43:00.260 align:middle line:84%
And even though sometimes
we don't intentionally

00:43:00.260 --> 00:43:01.587 align:middle line:90%
try to panic people--

00:43:01.587 --> 00:43:02.170 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: No.

00:43:02.170 --> 00:43:05.530 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: --government, I think,
has used it in order to do

00:43:05.530 --> 00:43:06.030 align:middle line:90%
things.

00:43:06.030 --> 00:43:08.950 align:middle line:84%
I'll always remember
the tragedy of 9/11

00:43:08.950 --> 00:43:13.420 align:middle line:84%
and that color-coded system,
which I was so opposed to.

00:43:13.420 --> 00:43:19.570 align:middle line:84%
Every day you heard code
yellow, code red, and people

00:43:19.570 --> 00:43:21.762 align:middle line:90%
were just paranoid about that.

00:43:21.762 --> 00:43:22.470 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Right.

00:43:22.470 --> 00:43:23.760 align:middle line:90%
And look what it did.

00:43:23.760 --> 00:43:26.125 align:middle line:84%
We passed the
so-called Patriot Act.

00:43:26.125 --> 00:43:27.000 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Absolutely.

00:43:27.000 --> 00:43:30.240 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: And 99 senators
stood up and voted for that.

00:43:30.240 --> 00:43:33.800 align:middle line:84%
And yet within the year when
everyone calmed back down--

00:43:33.800 --> 00:43:37.350 align:middle line:84%
including the Senate, see,
were affected by fear--

00:43:37.350 --> 00:43:41.982 align:middle line:84%
over 300 local governments
said, hey, what are we doing?

00:43:41.982 --> 00:43:42.940 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: That's right.

00:43:42.940 --> 00:43:44.560 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: And yet
it's still there.

00:43:44.560 --> 00:43:46.460 align:middle line:84%
Through the Bush
administration, through

00:43:46.460 --> 00:43:48.670 align:middle line:84%
the current administration,
nothing's changed.

00:43:48.670 --> 00:43:49.420 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: More so.

00:43:49.420 --> 00:43:50.490 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Absolutely.

00:43:50.490 --> 00:43:55.470 align:middle line:84%
More intrusions into our
lives than ever before,

00:43:55.470 --> 00:43:58.860 align:middle line:84%
and the general sense of
anxiety higher than ever before.

00:43:58.860 --> 00:44:01.590 align:middle line:84%
And this is inhibiting our
capacity as human beings

00:44:01.590 --> 00:44:03.894 align:middle line:84%
to not only solve our
problems but to awaken

00:44:03.894 --> 00:44:05.060 align:middle line:90%
to our higher possibilities.

00:44:05.060 --> 00:44:06.620 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: People are
wound up like a spring.

00:44:06.620 --> 00:44:08.453 align:middle line:84%
Let's take another
question for Nick Begich.

00:44:08.453 --> 00:44:09.870 align:middle line:90%
Yes, sir, right over here.

00:44:09.870 --> 00:44:12.580 align:middle line:84%
>> AUDIENCE: Back on the
thought of the HAARP affecting

00:44:12.580 --> 00:44:15.990 align:middle line:84%
the weather, I was wondering if
there's any connection at all

00:44:15.990 --> 00:44:21.130 align:middle line:84%
of the possibility of HAARP
causing any of these loud booms

00:44:21.130 --> 00:44:23.920 align:middle line:84%
and noises that's been going
on around America that Linda

00:44:23.920 --> 00:44:26.630 align:middle line:84%
Moulton Howe has
been investigating.

00:44:26.630 --> 00:44:28.850 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: I understand
that that's occurring,

00:44:28.850 --> 00:44:33.330 align:middle line:84%
but I don't how you might create
an acoustic signal using HAARP.

00:44:33.330 --> 00:44:34.970 align:middle line:84%
I just don't have
that information.

00:44:34.970 --> 00:44:35.880 align:middle line:90%
But I appreciate the question.

00:44:35.880 --> 00:44:38.060 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Something's going
on around this planet.

00:44:38.060 --> 00:44:39.230 align:middle line:90%
He's absolutely right.

00:44:39.230 --> 00:44:41.570 align:middle line:84%
And the stories that Linda's
been reporting on Coast

00:44:41.570 --> 00:44:44.590 align:middle line:84%
to Coast, all around
the country, probably

00:44:44.590 --> 00:44:47.962 align:middle line:84%
the planet, people are
hearing these loud explosions.

00:44:47.962 --> 00:44:48.670 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Right.

00:44:48.670 --> 00:44:51.480 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: I don't know
if something's blowing up

00:44:51.480 --> 00:44:54.970 align:middle line:84%
in the atmosphere or whether
it's a meteor, meteorite,

00:44:54.970 --> 00:44:56.641 align:middle line:90%
but something's happening.

00:44:56.641 --> 00:44:58.890 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: There's a lot of
things that could possibly

00:44:58.890 --> 00:45:03.250 align:middle line:84%
explain it, stealth aircraft
now passing through the sound

00:45:03.250 --> 00:45:03.750 align:middle line:90%
barrier.

00:45:03.750 --> 00:45:04.480 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Yeah.

00:45:04.480 --> 00:45:06.270 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: This kind of
technology is out there.

00:45:06.270 --> 00:45:06.670 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Maybe.

00:45:06.670 --> 00:45:08.350 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: There's
a lot going on.

00:45:08.350 --> 00:45:11.460 align:middle line:84%
So a lot of what happens,
too, with military

00:45:11.460 --> 00:45:15.000 align:middle line:84%
is how they sort of tell
the public don't worry.

00:45:15.000 --> 00:45:16.890 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the UFO
phenomenon is a big one.

00:45:16.890 --> 00:45:19.120 align:middle line:84%
Because when they
experiment with aircraft

00:45:19.120 --> 00:45:20.830 align:middle line:90%
that's sort of the default.

00:45:20.830 --> 00:45:21.330 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Those cases go way up.

00:45:21.330 --> 00:45:21.450 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: It's this.

00:45:21.450 --> 00:45:22.210 align:middle line:90%
It's not us.

00:45:22.210 --> 00:45:23.110 align:middle line:90%
It's the other guy.

00:45:23.110 --> 00:45:25.510 align:middle line:84%
But a lot of it is us, and
a lot of these phenomena

00:45:25.510 --> 00:45:29.412 align:middle line:84%
that people report,
it's us doing something.

00:45:29.412 --> 00:45:30.620 align:middle line:90%
It's not a natural phenomena.

00:45:30.620 --> 00:45:34.540 align:middle line:84%
Because all of a sudden it
occurs in a frame of time,

00:45:34.540 --> 00:45:37.470 align:middle line:90%
not before, not after, but here.

00:45:37.470 --> 00:45:39.490 align:middle line:84%
This is where experiments
are taking place.

00:45:39.490 --> 00:45:42.600 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: I'm sure as people saw
drones 10 years ago when they

00:45:42.600 --> 00:45:44.370 align:middle line:90%
were experimenting with them.

00:45:44.370 --> 00:45:46.264 align:middle line:84%
And they look like
UFOs, don't they?

00:45:46.264 --> 00:45:47.180 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Absolutely.

00:45:47.180 --> 00:45:49.250 align:middle line:84%
And they have all
different configurations,

00:45:49.250 --> 00:45:53.180 align:middle line:84%
drones from the size of
insects all the way up

00:45:53.180 --> 00:45:57.730 align:middle line:84%
to the large drones
being used in combat.

00:45:57.730 --> 00:46:00.256 align:middle line:84%
And it was in the literature
over 10 years ago.

00:46:00.256 --> 00:46:01.880 align:middle line:84%
There just weren't
many of them around.

00:46:01.880 --> 00:46:04.647 align:middle line:84%
But anybody who saw this kind
of stuff would say, what's that?

00:46:04.647 --> 00:46:06.480 align:middle line:84%
The military is going
to deny its existence,

00:46:06.480 --> 00:46:09.300 align:middle line:84%
but at the same time
you sort of default,

00:46:09.300 --> 00:46:13.700 align:middle line:84%
and, again, how people
default to this other picture.

00:46:13.700 --> 00:46:15.229 align:middle line:90%
UFOs become part of that.

00:46:15.229 --> 00:46:17.270 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: I suspect what
if something's happening

00:46:17.270 --> 00:46:21.290 align:middle line:84%
to the core of the planet and
it's creating these vibrations

00:46:21.290 --> 00:46:22.680 align:middle line:90%
and these explosions?

00:46:22.680 --> 00:46:26.720 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: Well, prior to
earthquakes you get extremely

00:46:26.720 --> 00:46:30.240 align:middle line:84%
low frequency signals that if
you monitor them-- in fact,

00:46:30.240 --> 00:46:32.170 align:middle line:84%
one of our authors,
Elizabeth Rauscher,

00:46:32.170 --> 00:46:34.500 align:middle line:84%
she's a geophysicist
and an astrophysicist,

00:46:34.500 --> 00:46:37.021 align:middle line:84%
is doing a book on earthquake
modeling and prediction.

00:46:37.021 --> 00:46:38.520 align:middle line:84%
But the idea that
the Earth is going

00:46:38.520 --> 00:46:40.710 align:middle line:84%
through huge and
dramatic changes,

00:46:40.710 --> 00:46:42.450 align:middle line:84%
I think we all can
acknowledge that.

00:46:42.450 --> 00:46:44.020 align:middle line:90%
We've seen it.

00:46:44.020 --> 00:46:46.302 align:middle line:84%
How that all connects
is what we haven't seen.

00:46:46.302 --> 00:46:48.260 align:middle line:84%
And it's because of the
way we compartmentalize

00:46:48.260 --> 00:46:51.170 align:middle line:84%
our science, geophysicists
looking at this,

00:46:51.170 --> 00:46:53.450 align:middle line:84%
and you've got astrophysicists
looking at that.

00:46:53.450 --> 00:46:55.720 align:middle line:84%
They all need to get
together and start

00:46:55.720 --> 00:46:58.970 align:middle line:84%
talking about the phenomena
and how they interact,

00:46:58.970 --> 00:47:00.480 align:middle line:84%
and that needs to
happen more often.

00:47:00.480 --> 00:47:02.665 align:middle line:84%
In fact, military
science in our country

00:47:02.665 --> 00:47:05.030 align:middle line:84%
is compartmentalized,
separated deliberately.

00:47:05.030 --> 00:47:07.590 align:middle line:84%
In the former Soviet Union,
it was blended in the way

00:47:07.590 --> 00:47:09.590 align:middle line:90%
that I'm talking about now.

00:47:09.590 --> 00:47:12.941 align:middle line:84%
And the blending of it
gave us a real adversary.

00:47:12.941 --> 00:47:15.190 align:middle line:84%
They didn't have the money
or the production capacity,

00:47:15.190 --> 00:47:17.030 align:middle line:84%
but they had really
good science,

00:47:17.030 --> 00:47:19.520 align:middle line:84%
because they benefited by
that cross-fertilization

00:47:19.520 --> 00:47:20.472 align:middle line:90%
between disciplines.

00:47:20.472 --> 00:47:21.430 align:middle line:90%
And we don't have that.

00:47:21.430 --> 00:47:24.610 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's, again,
one of the big missing links

00:47:24.610 --> 00:47:27.570 align:middle line:84%
for looking at all these
various drivers, including

00:47:27.570 --> 00:47:28.800 align:middle line:90%
climate change.

00:47:28.800 --> 00:47:30.370 align:middle line:90%
What all contributes to that?

00:47:30.370 --> 00:47:33.006 align:middle line:84%
We hear from atmospheric
scientists one thing.

00:47:33.006 --> 00:47:34.880 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps there's other
mechanisms that we just

00:47:34.880 --> 00:47:36.094 align:middle line:90%
don't understand quite yet.

00:47:36.094 --> 00:47:38.010 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: You brought a
sound device with you,

00:47:38.010 --> 00:47:38.890 align:middle line:90%
and we're going to look at that.

00:47:38.890 --> 00:47:40.390 align:middle line:84%
We're going to
conduct an experiment

00:47:40.390 --> 00:47:42.590 align:middle line:84%
in just a moment
on "Beyond Belief."

00:47:42.590 --> 00:47:46.220 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:47:46.220 --> 00:47:46.928 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Great.

00:47:46.928 --> 00:47:51.266 align:middle line:90%


00:47:51.266 --> 00:47:53.400 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: And welcome
back to "Beyond Belief."

00:47:53.400 --> 00:47:55.770 align:middle line:84%
I'm George Noory, of course,
with our guest Nick Begich.

00:47:55.770 --> 00:47:57.200 align:middle line:90%
Nick, you brought us some toys.

00:47:57.200 --> 00:47:57.520 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Right.

00:47:57.520 --> 00:47:58.950 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: What are these things?

00:47:58.950 --> 00:48:00.880 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: What I've
got is a sound wave.

00:48:00.880 --> 00:48:03.507 align:middle line:84%
This was developed by
my colleague in Germany.

00:48:03.507 --> 00:48:05.590 align:middle line:84%
And we used it actually
in the European Parliament

00:48:05.590 --> 00:48:07.860 align:middle line:84%
to demonstrate this
whole idea of infrasound,

00:48:07.860 --> 00:48:10.480 align:middle line:84%
the idea of putting
sound into the body

00:48:10.480 --> 00:48:14.170 align:middle line:84%
from an external signal, but one
that doesn't involve the ears.

00:48:14.170 --> 00:48:17.909 align:middle line:84%
So this we used to
demonstrate and to show this.

00:48:17.909 --> 00:48:20.450 align:middle line:84%
And at the same time, what we
ended up with from the European

00:48:20.450 --> 00:48:23.590 align:middle line:84%
Parliament was not just a
resolution opposing HAARP

00:48:23.590 --> 00:48:27.830 align:middle line:84%
but also standing in the way of
manipulation of human beings.

00:48:27.830 --> 00:48:30.310 align:middle line:84%
And this was important
for us as a threshold.

00:48:30.310 --> 00:48:32.280 align:middle line:90%
But it's a demonstration.

00:48:32.280 --> 00:48:33.850 align:middle line:84%
In the earlier
segment, we talked

00:48:33.850 --> 00:48:35.850 align:middle line:84%
about Woody Norris is
doing this wirelessly.

00:48:35.850 --> 00:48:37.100 align:middle line:90%
This is the hardwired version.

00:48:37.100 --> 00:48:37.940 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: This is the hardwire.

00:48:37.940 --> 00:48:38.648 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Right.

00:48:38.648 --> 00:48:40.971 align:middle line:84%
And this is a very
simple circuit.

00:48:40.971 --> 00:48:42.720 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: What kind
of sound does it emit?

00:48:42.720 --> 00:48:46.210 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: Well, what I've got
is I'm using a regular disc

00:48:46.210 --> 00:48:48.389 align:middle line:84%
player, so I've got some
Bach playing on this.

00:48:48.389 --> 00:48:48.930 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: OK.

00:48:48.930 --> 00:48:49.150 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: OK.

00:48:49.150 --> 00:48:51.040 align:middle line:84%
So what's going to
happen is this sound

00:48:51.040 --> 00:48:53.260 align:middle line:84%
goes through our
circuit and then comes

00:48:53.260 --> 00:48:55.250 align:middle line:90%
out these two transducers.

00:48:55.250 --> 00:48:57.200 align:middle line:84%
And these are
piezoelectric transducers,

00:48:57.200 --> 00:48:59.920 align:middle line:84%
so what they create is a little
bit of a drumming affect.

00:48:59.920 --> 00:49:03.670 align:middle line:84%
So you'll hear with the external
ear a little bit of sound.

00:49:03.670 --> 00:49:07.600 align:middle line:84%
So I'll ask our volunteer
to block their ears.

00:49:07.600 --> 00:49:10.880 align:middle line:84%
And then what will happen
is the sound will transit

00:49:10.880 --> 00:49:12.441 align:middle line:84%
through either the
nervous system--

00:49:12.441 --> 00:49:14.940 align:middle line:84%
it could be another energetic
system of the body-- it enters

00:49:14.940 --> 00:49:16.920 align:middle line:84%
the brain, and you
perceive the sound.

00:49:16.920 --> 00:49:21.280 align:middle line:84%
You'll hear Bach music as if it
were emanating from internally

00:49:21.280 --> 00:49:24.470 align:middle line:84%
inside of your head as opposed
to an external signal normally

00:49:24.470 --> 00:49:26.860 align:middle line:90%
coming in from the ear.

00:49:26.860 --> 00:49:30.800 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Once you do it, what
happens to the human being?

00:49:30.800 --> 00:49:31.720 align:middle line:90%
What's the purpose?

00:49:31.720 --> 00:49:34.800 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: In this case, this
was developed for a couple

00:49:34.800 --> 00:49:35.600 align:middle line:90%
things.

00:49:35.600 --> 00:49:37.875 align:middle line:84%
With a slightly
different signal,

00:49:37.875 --> 00:49:39.750 align:middle line:84%
you could actually use
this for certain kinds

00:49:39.750 --> 00:49:41.040 align:middle line:90%
of hearing impairments.

00:49:41.040 --> 00:49:44.027 align:middle line:84%
But you would need a
much different signal

00:49:44.027 --> 00:49:45.360 align:middle line:90%
than what we generate currently.

00:49:45.360 --> 00:49:47.170 align:middle line:84%
And the reason we
don't with this device

00:49:47.170 --> 00:49:48.740 align:middle line:90%
is it creates RF interference.

00:49:48.740 --> 00:49:51.725 align:middle line:84%
It'll mess with your cameras,
mess with your microphones.

00:49:51.725 --> 00:49:53.600 align:middle line:84%
Until we can figure out
a way to shield that,

00:49:53.600 --> 00:49:56.060 align:middle line:84%
we really can't explore
that application.

00:49:56.060 --> 00:49:59.590 align:middle line:84%
But it sends energy
through the body,

00:49:59.590 --> 00:50:03.000 align:middle line:84%
so the mind will actually
lock onto the signal.

00:50:03.000 --> 00:50:04.750 align:middle line:84%
You can use this for
accelerated learning,

00:50:04.750 --> 00:50:08.000 align:middle line:84%
for instance, by putting
learning information in here.

00:50:08.000 --> 00:50:08.750 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Amazing.

00:50:08.750 --> 00:50:10.570 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: So any
audio information.

00:50:10.570 --> 00:50:13.530 align:middle line:84%
You can also take
people in a circle,

00:50:13.530 --> 00:50:16.120 align:middle line:90%
and this requires contact.

00:50:16.120 --> 00:50:18.083 align:middle line:84%
And you'll hear a
slight demodulation.

00:50:18.083 --> 00:50:19.124 align:middle line:90%
Maybe people can hear it.

00:50:19.124 --> 00:50:20.165 align:middle line:90%
[CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:50:20.165 --> 00:50:21.080 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Maybe not.

00:50:21.080 --> 00:50:24.260 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: If you wanted
to learn a language,

00:50:24.260 --> 00:50:28.070 align:middle line:84%
could you use a system like
this and go to sleep with it on?

00:50:28.070 --> 00:50:30.400 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: Not so much sleep,
but you could certainly--

00:50:30.400 --> 00:50:31.804 align:middle line:90%
you're not going to focus on it.

00:50:31.804 --> 00:50:32.720 align:middle line:90%
You're going to relax.

00:50:32.720 --> 00:50:36.130 align:middle line:84%
You're going to let the
mind fall into its most

00:50:36.130 --> 00:50:37.126 align:middle line:90%
relaxed states.

00:50:37.126 --> 00:50:39.250 align:middle line:84%
And then you're essentially
feeding programming in,

00:50:39.250 --> 00:50:41.132 align:middle line:84%
and you're in control
of that programming.

00:50:41.132 --> 00:50:43.340 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of other
technologies that can do this.

00:50:43.340 --> 00:50:46.040 align:middle line:84%
Light and sound
devices can do this.

00:50:46.040 --> 00:50:49.885 align:middle line:84%
Certain signals can create
that accelerated learning

00:50:49.885 --> 00:50:50.385 align:middle line:90%
possibility.

00:50:50.385 --> 00:50:52.180 align:middle line:90%
This is just one of them.

00:50:52.180 --> 00:50:53.930 align:middle line:84%
But that, again, is
one of the areas where

00:50:53.930 --> 00:50:56.810 align:middle line:84%
I get really excited, the idea
of linking people together

00:50:56.810 --> 00:50:59.420 align:middle line:84%
where they're all harmonizing
at the same signal.

00:50:59.420 --> 00:51:01.250 align:middle line:84%
You can do this with
this kind of device,

00:51:01.250 --> 00:51:04.289 align:middle line:84%
which creates some
possibilities experimentally

00:51:04.289 --> 00:51:05.580 align:middle line:90%
that can be pretty interesting.

00:51:05.580 --> 00:51:07.560 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: So this is the
good part of the experiment?

00:51:07.560 --> 00:51:07.920 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Yeah.

00:51:07.920 --> 00:51:09.545 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: What's the
dark side of this?

00:51:09.545 --> 00:51:11.960 align:middle line:84%
>> BEGICH: The dark side of
this is think about this from

00:51:11.960 --> 00:51:15.600 align:middle line:84%
the wireless application, where
you can target an individual

00:51:15.600 --> 00:51:16.100 align:middle line:90%
in a crowd.

00:51:16.100 --> 00:51:18.120 align:middle line:84%
Well, all of a sudden
they hear the voice of God

00:51:18.120 --> 00:51:19.620 align:middle line:84%
talking to them to
go do something.

00:51:19.620 --> 00:51:21.010 align:middle line:84%
And they're saying,
hey, don't you hear it?

00:51:21.010 --> 00:51:21.360 align:middle line:90%
Don't you hear it?

00:51:21.360 --> 00:51:22.580 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: And
they've got that now.

00:51:22.580 --> 00:51:23.940 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: They have that now.

00:51:23.940 --> 00:51:26.700 align:middle line:84%
And everyone around them
goes, no, we don't hear it.

00:51:26.700 --> 00:51:28.700 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: You could
literally target one person?

00:51:28.700 --> 00:51:29.230 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Absolutely.

00:51:29.230 --> 00:51:29.890 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Or the masses?

00:51:29.890 --> 00:51:30.848 align:middle line:90%
>> BEGICH: Or the mass.

00:51:30.848 --> 00:51:33.240 align:middle line:90%


00:51:33.240 --> 00:51:34.770 align:middle line:84%
So you had these
things break out,

00:51:34.770 --> 00:51:37.600 align:middle line:84%
like we were talking about
earlier where somebody acts out

00:51:37.600 --> 00:51:39.381 align:middle line:90%
in a really bizarre way.

00:51:39.381 --> 00:51:41.130 align:middle line:84%
They say, well, it was
a voice in my head.

00:51:41.130 --> 00:51:44.720 align:middle line:84%
Well, was it psychosis
or was it technology?

00:51:44.720 --> 00:51:47.260 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: If you wanted
to experiment on someone,

00:51:47.260 --> 00:51:51.740 align:middle line:84%
